    <h1>Biography</h1>

    <p>Hi, my name is Darius and I'm currently an undergraduate at UIC pursing a BS in computer science. Along with this, I also work as a research assistant on-campus. I currently am assisting <a href="https://kshind2.people.uic.edu">Komal Shinde</a> under Professor <a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/~brents/">Brent Stephens</a>. Specifically, I am currently researching Barefoot Tofino programmable switch configurations in P4 regarding ECN congestion and logical queues.</p>


